m any variables?\nAre there NA values, outliers or other strange values?\nShould I create new variables?\n\nFor the rest of this lesson we will address each of these questions.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"\"PassengerId\" is just a number assigned to each passenger. It is nothing more than an arbitrary identifier. We could keep it for identification purposes, but lets remove it anyway.\n\ntitanic_train$PassengerId  <- NULL   # Remove PassengerId","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"titanic$PassengerId  <- NULL","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-11-28T11:16:10.031853Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-11-28T11:16:10.034305Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-11-28T11:16:10.052005Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":7,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"We just removed the column passengerid you can check the data by printing the first 25 lines","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"","metadata":{},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"1\"></a>\n<font color=\"purple\" size=+2.5><b>Compare Means- T-Test</b></font>\n\n<a href=\"#top\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-sm\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"true\" style=\"color:white\" data-toggle=\"popover\" title=\"go to Colors\">Go to TOC</a>\n# Performs one or multiple mean comparisons.\n\ncompare_means(\n  formula,\n  data,\n  method = \"wilcox.test\",\n  paired = FALSE,\n  group.by = NULL,\n  ref.group = NULL,\n  symnum.args = list(),\n  p.adjust.method = \"holm\",\n  ...\n)\n[Details and examples on how to use compare_means](https://rpkgs.datanovia.com/ggpubr/reference/compare_means.html)\n\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Is there a significant difference between male and female passenger fare?\nLets try a t.test to see what the p value","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"compare_means(Fare ~ Sex, data = titanic)\n\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-11-28T11:29:53.128058Z","iopub.e