ype":"markdown","source":"**Purpose** : Relationship between numerical values.\n\n**Question** : Is age related to fare of titanic passengers?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig(12,8)\nggplot(titanic, aes(x=Age, y=Fare)) + \n  geom_point() + \n  labs(y=\"Fare\", \n       x=\"Age\", \n       title=\"Titanic - Age vs Fare\")+\n        theme_gray()+\n       theme(plot.title = element_text(size=22),axis.text.x= element_text(size=15),\n                            axis.text.y= element_text(size=15), axis.title=element_text(size=18))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-11-20T18:11:43.117224Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-11-20T18:11:43.119078Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-11-20T18:11:43.489945Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"2\"></a>\n<font color=\"purple\" size=+2.5><b>2. Scatter plot - Category</b></font>\n\n<a href=\"#top\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-sm\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"true\" style=\"color:white\" data-toggle=\"popover\" title=\"go to Colors\">Go to TOC</a>","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Purpose** : Relationship between numerical values with a categorical field.\n\n**Question** : Is age related to fare of titanic passengers with respective to gender?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"t.test(x = titanic$Sex, y = titanic$Fare,conf.level=0.95)\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-11-21T13:49:35.430537Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-11-21T13:49:35.432119Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-11-21T13:49:35.536512Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig(12,8)\nggplot(titanic, aes(x=Age, y=Fare)) + \n  geom_point(aes(color=Sex)) + \n  labs(y=\"Fare\", \n       x=\"Age\", \n       title=\"Titanic - Age vs Fare against Gender \")+ \n       theme_gray()+ # Default theme \n        theme(plot.title = element_text(size=22),axis.text.x= element_text(size=15),\n                            axis.text.y= element_text(size=15), axis.title=element_text(size=18))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-11-20T18:27:12.951289Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-11-20T18:27:12.953009Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-11-20T18:27:13.413700Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"3\"></a>\n<font color=\"purple\" size=+2.5><b>3. Scatter plot - Color and Size</b></font>\n\n<a href=\"#top\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-sm\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"true\" style=\"color:white\" data-toggle=\"popover\" title=\"go to Colors\">Go to TOC</a>","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Purpose** :  Relationship between numerical values with addition of categorization by a field and increasing size of datapoint by another numerical field.\n\n**Question** : How much dependency between Quality of Education and Students Score for different countries based on number of students?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig(15,8)\nggplot(university, aes(x=quality_of_education, y=score)) + \n  geom_point(aes(color=country,size=citations)) + \n  labs(x=\"Quality Of Education\", \n       y=\"Score\",\n       title=\"Quality of Education Vs Score against Country & Citations\")+ \n        theme_linedraw()+\n       theme(plot.title = element_text(size=22),axis.text.x= element_text(size=15),\n                            axis.text.y= element_text(size=15), axis.title=element_text(size=18))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-11-20T18:12:32.479357Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-11-20T18:12:32.481662Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-11-20T18:12:35.312518Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"compare_means(score ~ country, data = university)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-11-22T13:44:52.678225Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-11-22T13:44:52.679750Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-11-22T13:44:53.808797Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"4\"></a>\n<font color=\"purple\" size=+2.5><b>4. Scatter - Color Dimension</b></font>\n\n<a href=\"#top\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-sm\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"true\" style=\"color:white\" data-toggle=\"popover\" title=\"go to Colors\">Go to TOC</a>","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Purpose** :  Relationship between numerical values exposing most data points by color gradient.\n\n**Question** : How much relationship between Days associated with Company vs Amount to be paid with respective to Age of Customers?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig(12,8)\nggplot(sample_n(insurance, 500), aes(x=Vintage,y=Annual_Premium,color=Age)) +\n  geom_point()+\n    scale_color_gradient(low = 'yellow', high = 'red')+\n    labs(y=\"Insurance Amount\", \n       x=\"Days associated with Company\", \n       title=\"Days associated with Company vs Amount to be paid against Age of Customer \")+ \n       theme_dark()+ # Dark Theme\n      theme(plot.title = element_text(size=22),axis.text.x= element_text(size=15),\n                            axis.text.y= element_text(size=15), axis.title=element_text(size=18))","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"5\"></a>\n<font color=\"purple\" size=+2.5><b>5. Jitter Plot</b></font>\n\n<a href=\"#top\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-sm\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"true\" style=\"color:white\" data-toggle=\"popover\" title=\"go to Colors\">Go to TOC</a>","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Purpose** :  Relationship between numerical values exposing most data points by color gradient with jitter points.\n\n**Question** : How much relationship between Area and Price with respective to Lotshape of houses? (Apply Jitter points)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig(12,8)\nggplot(house, aes(x=LotArea,y=SalePrice,color=LotShape)) +\n  geom_jitter(width = .5, size=2)+  # Adjusting size and width of points\n    labs(x=\"Area\",\n         y=\"Sales Price\", \n       title=\"Lot Area vs House Price against LotShape \")+ \ntheme_bw()+\ntheme(plot.title = element_text(size=22),axis.text.x= element_text(size=15),\n                            axis.text.y= element_text(size=15), axis.title=element_text(size=18))","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"6\"></a>\n<font color=\"purple\" size=+2.5><b>6. Jitter & Encircling Points</b></font>\n\n<a href=\"#top\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-sm\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"true\" style=\"color:white\" data-toggle=\"popover\" title=\"go to Colors\">Go to TOC</a>","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Purpose** :  Relationship between numerical values exposing most data points by color gradient with jitter points and encircle dots based on condition.\n\n**Question** : How much relationship between Area and Price with respective to Lotshape of houses and encircle costlier houses?","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"costly_price_with_less_area<-house[house$SalePrice>600000 & house$LotArea<25000,]\n\nfig(12,8)\nggplot(house, aes(x=LotArea,y=SalePrice,color=LotShape)) +\n  geom_jitter(width = .5, size=2)+ # Adjusting size and width of points\n  geom_encircle(aes(x=LotArea, y=SalePrice), \n                data=costly_price_with_less_area, \n                color=\"red\", \n                size=2, \n                expand=0.08)+\n    labs(x=\"Area\",\n         y=\"Sales Price\", \n       title=\"Lot Area vs House Price (Circle Costlier House with Less Area) \")+ \ntheme_bw()+\ntheme(plot.title = element_text(size=22),axis.text.x= element_text(size=15),\n                            axis.text.y= element_text(size=15), axis.title=element_text(size=18))","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<a id=\"7\"></a>\n<font color=\"steelblue\" size=+2.5><b>7. 